The paper focuses on introducing novel non-invasive early diagnosis methods for Alzheimer's Disease using virtual environments and emotion recognition. This involves the use of advanced Human Computer Interaction (HCI) systems, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also introduces new descriptors for Electroencephalogram (EEG) and facial images data, which can be used for classification, falling under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses classifiers such as SVM and Adaboost, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
